<div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
<p>The complete text copied by Sherard in 1716 (f.126v) and Rochette; by Deering ( f 6v, no.27); by Fellows (perhaps by Bailie); by Choisy. Fragment of ll. 7-9 copied by K&amp;R (R.I.6); fragment recorded by Gaudin (no number); three larger fragments (a, b and c) recorded by the MAMA expedition (all discussed by Cormack, Notes 17 and 62 fig. 11); a and b recorded by the NYU expedition in 1972.</p>
</div>
